5:
Stella, what do you think about this
one?
8:
I don't understand. Why does
everyone always recommend
clothes with insufficient surface
area to cover one's body?
13:
Don't you think this looks cute
though? Actually, judging by that
reaction, maybe not...
17:
Are there any stores around here
that you're into? I'd love to give them
a look too.
20:
...I thought you were supposed to be
working today.
24:
It's fiiine, don't worry about it. Unlike
back home, there's no one here
breathing down my neck. Besides,
I'm not completely slacking off.
Watch this.
31:
Hmm... Town's been relatively quiet
lately, then?
34:
You got it. No reports of anything
strange or sketchy. Just some rare
peace and quiet.
36:
Anyway, your order's ready. Always
appreciate you stopping by!
39:
Thanks! I'll be sure to drop by again
sometime!
44:
You see now? I'm still working, even
if it might not look like it.
47:
Merchants are a great way to
gather info, since they travel around
a lot and always have their ears to
the ground.
54:
Back home, there's this one
particular merchant I deal with all
the time... But it's almost scary how
her eyes and ears are everywhere...
62:
Nope, it's yours. Consider it thanks
for keeping me company today.
64:
Work hard, play hard, remember? 
I always get the job done, but on the
flipside, I'll take advantage of any
downtime I have.
72: Hey there, ladies. Out grabbin' info?
74:
Have I got the juicy scoop for you.
Follow me, and I'll show you
something you won't want to miss.
80:
Stella, you head back first. I'll go see
what this is about.
88:
All right, I know a scam when I see
one. What's this really about?
91:
Heh, you followed us knowing this
was a setup? You've got some guts.
93:
That spear of yours looks like it'd sell
for a pretty penny.
95:
Hand it over, and nobody's gonna
get hurt.
103:
At least you had the decency not to
take my friend hostage, I'll give you
that.
107:
But if you think you can take me out
because there's two of you and only
one of me, you've got another thing
coming.
113:
Neither of you stand a chance
against Arvess. If you know what's
good for you, you'll cut your losses
and run.
122: Stella?! What are you doing here?
137:
...Pffft, hahaha! That's what I should
be asking you!
141:
But I appreciate the concern. I'm
actually kinda touched.
145:
I gave you a chance to turn tail and
run.
149:
Now you've gone and threatened
my friend. I hope you're ready for
your just deserts.
156:
The only thing you'll be showing me
is your sorry faces buried in the
ground!
160:
That'll teach you to mess with Arvess
and me. Now get out of my sight.
169:
Sheesh, talk about putting yourself
right in the middle of it all. You're not
used to fighting, right?
171:
Next time, leave everything to me.
The last thing I want is for you to get
hurt on my behalf.
178:
I gotta say though, you moved
impressively fast. Don't tell me
you've been hiding some secret
fighting skills this whole time.
182:
No, not fighting skills. I can't fight,
because that involves moving my
arms and legs at the same time.
186:
However, I am used to acting quickly
to protect myself and avoid injury.
190:
Only evasive maneuvers in your
arsenal, huh? Still, that was pretty
awesome.
198:
Want to go for some more
shopping? I could really use another
round of stress relief after that.
200:
Don't wanna end today on a sour
note either.
203:
In that case, I want to shop for your
clothes this time, Zeta.
207:
Ohhh, that's a good idea! Choose an
outfit for me!
210:
I don't mind showing a bit of skin, so
go wild.
214: I see. I'll take that into consideration.
218:
Sweet, I can't wait to see what you
come up with!
